-- Zambia Metal Exports in June Fall to $389 Million, Reducing Trade Earnings
-- Obert Simwanza
-- 2010-07-29T10:14:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/zambia-metal-exports-in-june-fall-to-389-million-reducing-trade-earnings.html

          
          
             The value of Zambian metal exports
in June fell to 1.9 trillion kwacha from 2.35 trillion kwacha in
May, according to trade figures released by Central Statistical
Office Acting Director John Kalumbi in the Zambian capital,
Lusaka, today.  
 The overall contribution of metal products to total export
earnings by the country declined to 76.6 percent last month
compared with 80.4 percent in May, Kalumbi said. Exports of
copper and copper products, which amounted to 1.77 trillion
kwacha, accounted for 70.4 percent of total export earnings, he
said.  
          
          


  


        